    {
      "id": 2,
      "text": "The borough grew around a snuff mill opened in the 1820s, later purchased by George Washington Helme in the 1880s.",
      "sourceSentenceIds": [
        12
      ],
      "sourceLabels": [
        "Wikipedia"
      ],
      "source": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Helmetta%2C_New_Jersey"
    },
    {
      "id": 3,
      "text": "By 1925 the Helme Snuff Mill had become the world’s largest snuff producer, employing 400 people by 1934.",
      "sourceSentenceIds": [
        17
      ],
      "sourceLabels": [
        "Wikipedia"
      ],
      "source": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Helmetta%2C_New_Jersey"
    },
    {
      "id": 4,
      "text": "The historic mill district was added to the New Jersey Register of Historic Places and the National Register in 1980.",
